title: Bulldogs Outpace Huskies for Homecoming
text:
Bulldogs Outpace Huskies for Homecoming 
By Norman Seawright III October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 10:51 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The No. 25 University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) football team defeated St. Cloud State in front of a record crowd (6,157) for homecoming at Malosky Stadium. 
The Bulldogs struck first, scoring on a Jeremiah Newell goal line blast, then sealed the win between a forced fumble (leading to a Brent Stiglich interception/touchdown run) and a Drew Bauer run, leaving the Huskies to settle with a 34-27 loss.
